BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:N4s6jc9Iz7FykYywU-EeB
SUMMARY:PNA Woodshop\\\, dedicated to Bill Fenimore
DTSTAMP:20260307T061518Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260312T190000
DESCRIPTION:Did you know that there is a woodshop in your area? Whether you
	’re a newcomer to woodworking or an experienced woodworker\\\, the PNA woo
	dshop is the ideal place to bring your creative projects to life. Whether 
	you’re interested in crafting a bench\\\, flower bed\\\, jewelry box\\\, c
	hair\\\, or cupboard\\\, the possibilities are endless. All you need to do
	 is become a PNA member\\\, attend an orientation\\\, and complete two saf
	ety classes. Once you’ve done that\\\, you can reserve your shop time and 
	get started on your project.\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/pna-wo
	odshop-dedicated-to-bill-fenimore/2026-03-07/\n\nFrom Phinney Neighborhood
	 Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/pna-woodshop-dedicated-to-bill-feni
	more/2026-03-07/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Brick (lower) Building\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave
	. N.\\\, Seattle\\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT4H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:zYjfURe2FLuzv5b-vMcdl
SUMMARY:Fix-it Fair
DTSTAMP:20260307T061518Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/Los_Angeles:20260313T180000
DESCRIPTION:Bring your broken items to the Fix-it Fair. The PNA Fixers will
	 diagnose and repair your item for free (parts may be extra) while also he
	lping reduce waste in Seattle. At the same time\\\, you can bond with the 
	rest of your local community and learn something new by watching the repai
	r. Typical items include heaters\\\, sewing machines\\\, waffle irons\\\, 
	blenders\\\, mixers\\\, electric bikes\\\, extension cords\\\, lamps\\\, a
	udio gear\\\, and more. There are hardware stores nearby if you need to fe
	tch parts. There is also a professional knife sharpener on hand\\\, and we
	 expect to have sewists to mend and hem clothing. Walk-ins are welcome but
	 it’s helpful if you can RSVP to let us know what you’re bringing: bit.ly/
	GreenwoodFix-itFair. The PNA Fixers meet regularly at Greenwood Hardware o
	n the first Wednesday of every month\\\, 3–6 pm. \\nFree\\\, but donations
	 are appreciated. \\n\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/fix-it-fair/\
	n\nFrom Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/fix-it-fair/
LOCATION:Greenwood Senior Center\\\, 525 N. 85th St.\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\,
	 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:lXf45pvWnhxBO4G6n-0f8
SUMMARY:Kristian Bugge & Ruthie Dornfeld – 2 Fiddle masters play Danish & A
	merican music and more!
DTSTAMP:20260307T061518Z
DTSTART:20260307T193000Z
DESCRIPTION:Kristian Bugge (Denmark) and Ruthie Dornfeld (Seattle) will ent
	ertain us with a wide range of music including Danish traditional fiddle t
	unes and music from the other Nordic countries to old-time American and se
	lf-composed original tunes\\\, spiced up with a few Venezuelan waltzes.\\n
	Kristian and Ruthie first met each other in the Danish folk music circles 
	in the mid-1990’s\\\, where Ruthie had been touring regularly and growing 
	a reputation as a well-renowned artist and fiddler since the early 1980’s.
	 Later when Kristian was a music student\\\, Ruthie was guest-teaching at 
	the Carl Nielsen Academy of Music in Odense\\\, Denmark and Kristian made 
	sure to take the opportunity to study with her while she was there. About 
	ten years later they met again in and around Seattle when Kristian had sta
	rted touring and performing in the states. This summer marked a new chapte
	r in their collaboration and friendship as they started touring and record
	ing as a duo for the first time. Expect everything from wild polkas and ji
	gs to lyrical waltzes\\\, fiery reels and happy hopsas\\\, all served with
	 humor and stories from their many years on the road. The doors open at 7p
	m for the 7:30 cocnert in the phinney Community Hall (lower Brick Building
	). Advance tickets are $26/$24 members of SFS\\\, PNA\\\, or Skandia\\\, s
	tudents\\\, or seniors 65+/ $10 Youth to age 17\; at the door $2 more for 
	adults ($28/$26/$10).\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/event/kristian-bugg
	e-ruthie-dornfeld-2-fiddle-masters-play-danish-american-music-and-more/\n\
	nFrom Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/kristian-bugge-ruthie-dornfeld-2-fi
	ddle-masters-play-danish-american-music-and-more/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave. N.\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\
	\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
